gomodel:SYNGO_5440  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1d: KIF2C was expressed in all synaptic biochemical fractions prepared from mouse hippocampus, including synaptosomes, presynaptic fractions and PSD. Strongest enrichment was observed in the latter.\n\nFigure 1e: confocal immunofluorescence imaging of hippocampal neurons double-labeled for KIF2C and either PSD95 (DLG4) or Bassoon (BSN) showed partial co-localization with both marker proteins, suggesting KIF2C is localized to both pre- and post-synapse.. Experimental description: Results, Figure 1 legend: \"Subcellular distribution of KIF2C in mouse hippocampus.\"\n\nAntibody to KIF2C (12139-1-AP, RRID:AB_2877829) was purchased from Proteintech (Rosemont, IL)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5440" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

